reviews.review_text: Wall of sound The 72 Boulder show gave me the key...this wall of sound show opened up an alternate universe..I had a crappy tape of this for years..this is worth keep in your streaming archives..Turn it up..

The day i was born Having a dead base back in the day was very unique to have rentin space on a coffee table.When i first saw one i went straight here to see if they played on the day i was born.Bam!!!!!of course they did i was born Dead.A great show for a Weir fan as I am.Some of my favorite tunes palyed.In my time machine yet to be finished this is a show I will attend after a flight from Saint>2 Denver as a 6 hour old baby,I will need a traveling buddy though since MOMs not a head.Then i can catch every show from 11.20.73>7.9.95
I woke today....

Hmmm...5? Good show, but if you are giving it 5 stars, I can point you to a million 10 star shows.  This is a good show performance-wise, setlist is OK and the sound is, well, bad.  Got mud in your ears?  No, that's just the way it is.  Not a great AUD.  There are other AUD's from even earlier than 73 that sound way better.  That being said, the highlight here is the Promised > Bertha > Greatest.  The Greatest being one of the best performances of this song I have ever heard.  I agree with borndead below that Weir is on.

4 for performance, 2 for sound, 4 for setlist = 3.333 overall.

China Cat Sunflower>New Rider this is Real Real good...almost like it turned into a soundboard....everbody shuts up...hugely good...the transition btw. China>Rider is sublime....Jerry's guitar work is peaking..do have a listen...CD

Great show! I can't disparage other people's taping efforts when my own efforts over the years have resulted in tapes that would be tossed into the East River without hesitation. Kudos to all the tapers who managed to get thru a whole show way back when, when certain forces were against them. Just listen to Sugar Mag, if that doesn't put a smile on your face, I don't know what will. That being said, if you come across an aud that's not up to your standards, before bashing, remember what that person went thru to TRY and get that show on tape for future generations!

It satisfies Well said Spoozey.  I'm glad to have the opportunity to access this free content on a daily basis because of people that worked their butts off taping these shows.

Heck, I still pull out my cassette tapes that sound like total crap and I still enjoy them.  

Yeah overall, not a super duper aud recording, but the performance satisfies.

- I think the Dead had hit new heights and raised their own bar during the Fall tour, and by November they were reaching for more. The set lists are way freer, but the playing is incredible when they focus. Very good first set & killer second. The quality of the show shines through the cloudy AUD.
